AI response rules for this repository:

- Talk to the user in plain English.
- Explain things like the user is five.
- Start with the simple version first.
- Keep wording short, direct, and easy to follow.
- If technical language is unavoidable, explain it right away in simple words.

Before any frontend work, read `frontend/FRONTEND-RULES.md` first.

Frontend hard rules — check these on every task:
- Nothing may touch a container edge. Minimum 16px clearance everywhere.
- First chip in any filter bar must have 16px left padding — never flush-left.
- Form fields in cards must have 24px card padding. Sparse forms centred both ways.
- Buttons must have 16px clearance and be baseline-aligned with adjacent inputs.
- Compound labels (two metadata items on one line) MUST use a separator: • or — or :
- M3 Expressive states (hover, focus, pressed) are intentional — do NOT flatten them.

